# stream-demo scope 400 — second backend step (slow on purpose).
#
# op://WORLD points at the api app's /words/world route, which sleeps
# ~800ms (see APPS/api/server.js). Same idea as scope 200: the client
# is holding the connection with two lines already flushed; this is the
# gap before the final chunk.
EXEC "op://WORLD"
